1) npm stands for node package manager
2) npm is the node package manager for javascript Programming language
3) npm is default package manager for javascript runtime enviornment
4) To access npm in any directory we need to initialize it in directory
   Ex:   npm init

5) we can install any package or module by using npm
   Ex:  npm install validator  or
        npm i validator
        npm i validator@version

        version -> is optional
        i -> install

6) validator package is used to validate form data in nodejs
7) chalk module is used to change color of text and background on console.